<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2025</p>

<p>Tribal Goods Trail is operated by <strong>Real Nash Tech & Consulting (Woodburn, Oregon)</strong>.  
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We may collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Business submission details (name, owner, description, category, location)</li>
  <li>User-provided contact information (email only, if contacting us)</li>
  <li>Approximate location for “nearby businesses” features</li>
  <li>Crash logs, analytics, and performance data</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To display Native-owned businesses in the directory</li>
  <li>To verify authenticity of submissions</li>
  <li>To improve app performance and user experience</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Location Information</h2>
<p>Your device’s location is used only for calculating distance to businesses.  
No permanent storage of user location occurs.</p>

<h2>4. Business Submissions</h2>
<p>All submissions are manually reviewed. Information you submit may be displayed on the public directory once approved.</p>

<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share personal information with third parties.  
Anonymous analytics may be used to improve performance.</p>

<h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>Tribal Goods Trail is intended for general audiences and does not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>

<h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You may request removal or modification of your business listing at any time.</p>

<h2>8. Contact</h2>
<p>Email: <a href="mailto:a.gentry88@icloud.com">a.gentry88@icloud.com</a></p>

